        <h2 id="sugar-cookie">Sugar Cookies</h2>
        <img src="http://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/720x405/1754462.jpg" width="200" alt="Two sugar cookies">
        <ul>
            <li>Time: Approximately 25 mins</li>
            <li>Amount: 2 dozen cookies</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td> Flour </td>
                <td> 2 3/4 cups </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td> Sugar </td>
                <td> 1 1/2 cups </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td> Baking Soda </td>
                <td>  1 tsp</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td> Baking Powder </td>
                <td>  1/2 tsp</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td> Egg </td>
                <td>  1</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>  Vanilla Extract</td>
                <td> 1 tsp </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>  Butter</td>
                <td>  1 cup</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p id="sugar"><strong>Step 1:</strong> First preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda and set it aside.
<br>
     
      <strong>Step 2:</strong> Next, cream the butter and sugar together in a large bowl until smooth. Beat egg and vanilla extract into the mix. Gradually blend in dry ingredients. Roll teaspoonfuls into round balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheets.
     <br>
     <strong>Step 3:</strong> Bake for 8-10 minutes or until golden brown. Let it sit for 2 minutes before cooling on rack.</p>

    <h2 id="brownie">  Brownies</h2>
     <img src="http://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/487007.jpg" width="200" alt="A couple of brownies on a plain plate">
     <ul>
         <li>Time: About 40 mins </li>
         <li> Amount: Roughly 1 dozen</li>
     </ul>
     
     <table>
         <thead>
             <tr>
                 <th>Ingredients
                 <th>Quantity
             </tr>
         </thead>
         <tbody>
             <tr>
                 <td> Walnut Halves
                 <td> 1/2 cup
             </tr>
              <tr>
                 <td> Sugar </td>
                 <td> 2 cups
             </tr>
              <tr>
                 <td> Butter
                 <td> 1 cup
             </tr>
              <tr>
                 <td> Cocoa Powder
                 <td> 1/2 cup
             </tr>
              <tr>
                 <td> Vanilla Extract
                 <td> 1 tsp
             </tr>
              <tr>
                 <td> Eggs
                 <td> 4
             </tr>
              <tr>
                 <td> Flour
                 <td> 1 cup
             </tr>
              <tr>
                 <td> Baking Powder
                 <td> 1/2 tsp
             </tr>
              <tr>
                 <td> Salt
                 <td> 1/2 tsp
             </tr>
         </tbody>
     </table>
    
        <p id="chocolate"><strong> Step 1: </strong> 
            Firstly, melt the butter and mix in all the ingredients as in the order shown in 'Ingredients' (except for the walnut shells, which go in last).
        <br>
        
        <strong> Step 2:</strong>
        Bake in the oven for 350 degrees F for 20 - 30 minutes in a 9 x 13 inch greased pan. Leave to cool.
        </p>
        
        <h2 id= "ginger-snap"> Ginger Snaps</h2>
        <img src="http://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/532567.jpg" width="200" alt="An array of gingersnaps with icing">
        <ul>
            <li> Time: 20 mins
            <li> Amount: 1- 1 1/2 dozens
        </ul>
    
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th> Ingredients
                <th> Quantity
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td> Sugar
                <td> 1 cup
            </tr>
              <tr>
                <td> Egg
                <td> 1
            </tr>
              <tr>
                <td> Salt
                <td> 1/4 tsp
            </tr>
              <tr>
                <td> Softened Butter
                <td> 3/4 cups
            </tr>
              <tr>
                <td> Flour
                <td> 2 cups
            </tr>
              <tr>
                <td> Baking Soda
                <td> 1/4 tsp
            </tr>
              <tr>
                <td> Ground Cloves
                <td> 1 tsp
            </tr>
              <tr>
                <td> Ground Ginger
                <td> 1 tsp
            </tr>
              <tr>
                <td> Ground Cinnamon
                <td> 1 tsp
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <p id="ginger"><strong> Step 1:</strong>
        Preheat oven to 350 degrees F
  <br>
    
   <strong> Step 2:</strong>
        Cream the sugar, egg, salt and butter together until smooth. Add flour, baking soda and spices. Mix well. Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into balls and roll them in white sugar. 
   <br>
    
    <strong> Step 3:</strong>
        Bake in oven at 350 degrees F for 6 minutes.
    </p>
    
    <h2 id="contents"> Enjoy!</h2>
    
